00:55.765 --> 00:57.892
MAN: I was thinking
maybe you were a no-show.

00:58.059 --> 01:01.521
Middle of the day.
Hard to disentangle from work.

01:03.398 --> 01:05.692
So many flakes on the
message board. You never know.

01:05.859 --> 01:07.902
But you're here now.

01:10.196 --> 01:12.365
Let's see
what I'm working with here.

01:16.327 --> 01:18.037
You negative?

01:18.204 --> 01:19.539
Just tested.

01:19.706 --> 01:21.958
All top and popper-friendly.

01:22.125 --> 01:25.003
Just like the posting says.
(INHALES)

01:30.258 --> 01:31.760
(INHALES)

01:35.597 --> 01:38.892
(CRIES)

01:43.813 --> 01:46.524
No! No, Daddy! Daddy, no!

01:46.691 --> 01:49.402
Daddy, no!

01:49.569 --> 01:51.613
(SCREAMS)

01:59.329 --> 02:02.332
(THEME MUSIC)

02:49.420 --> 02:51.256
ROMAN ON PHONE: Hey. It's me.

02:51.422 --> 02:53.216
So listen.

02:54.259 --> 02:56.469
What happened yesterday
with that guy,

02:56.636 --> 02:58.555
it was a terrible thing, and...

02:58.721 --> 03:01.099
If I could
take it all back, I...

03:01.266 --> 03:04.060
But what happened
before the shooting with us,

03:04.227 --> 03:06.187
that was maybe
the most beautiful thing,

03:06.354 --> 03:08.064
at least for me.

03:08.231 --> 03:10.108
All the gunfire in the world
can't change that.

03:11.526 --> 03:13.570
I'll say a prayer for the guy.

03:13.736 --> 03:16.823
But call me back when you
get this, OK? I need to see you.

03:16.990 --> 03:19.075
It's me, Roman.

03:23.580 --> 03:26.291
<i>You've reached Andreas.
I can't take your call.</i>

03:26.457 --> 03:28.501
<i>- Please leave a message.
- (BEEP)</i>

03:28.668 --> 03:31.754
It's your fiancÃ©e calling,
again.

03:31.921 --> 03:34.549
Where are you? You were supposed
to be here two hours ago.

03:34.716 --> 03:36.551
Remember I bought you
a really expensive watch?

03:36.718 --> 03:40.763
How about you try using it
to tell the time? OK? Call me.

03:40.930 --> 03:43.016
(SIGHS)

03:43.182 --> 03:45.351
And if you ran off to Vegas
with some stripper...

03:46.811 --> 03:49.355
Just...call me back, you dummy.

03:49.522 --> 03:51.482
(PHONE BEEPS)

03:55.612 --> 03:57.780
- (TYRES SCREECH)
- Fuck!

04:03.703 --> 04:04.829
(GUN CLICKS)

04:14.297 --> 04:16.173
Directions to the body
if you want him back.

04:16.341 --> 04:17.966
If it was up to me,

04:18.134 --> 04:20.219
I'd leave that shithead
with the rats,

04:20.386 --> 04:22.305
just like the rest
of the garbage.

04:27.810 --> 04:29.646
(CAR DOORS CLOSE)

04:42.033 --> 04:43.910
PRYCE: Doesn't sound like
you want to be an upir

04:44.077 --> 04:46.120
living in East Cornwall.

04:47.830 --> 04:50.041
Those things just kept...coming.

04:50.208 --> 04:52.085
This is far worse
than I imagined.

04:52.251 --> 04:54.212
Things seem to have escalated
precipitously.

04:54.379 --> 04:58.007
Six weeks ago, Arnold Spivak MD
morphs into a...

04:58.174 --> 05:00.176
..flying reptoid.

05:00.343 --> 05:02.303
Then out of nowhere, this shit?

05:02.470 --> 05:05.932
- Are the two related?
- You got to ask the question.

05:06.099 --> 05:07.767
I've been wondering
the same thing

05:07.934 --> 05:09.560
and analysing
these autopsy results

05:09.727 --> 05:11.562
looking for any connection
to the Spivak genome.

05:11.729 --> 05:13.106
And?

05:13.272 --> 05:15.024
So far, nothing,

05:15.191 --> 05:17.193
but now that this evidence
has surfaced linking Spivak

05:17.360 --> 05:19.529
to genetic research
the Nazis were doing...

05:19.696 --> 05:22.281
- What evidence?
- Well, uh...

05:22.448 --> 05:24.742
What I meant to say
is I should, or, rather, I will,

05:24.909 --> 05:27.203
do some investigating,
see if there's...

05:27.370 --> 05:29.956
..evidence that Spivak WAS aware

05:30.123 --> 05:33.835
of the research the...
Nazis were doing.

05:34.877 --> 05:37.630
(CRUNCHES)

05:37.797 --> 05:39.298
That could tell us
something.

05:45.304 --> 05:48.975
I'm so glad you and Annie made it
back from East Cornwall OK.

05:49.142 --> 05:50.727
You were lucky.

05:50.893 --> 05:53.479
I make my own luck.

06:04.532 --> 06:06.325
(PHONE BEEPS)

06:06.492 --> 06:08.077
He's not answering texts
or returning calls,

06:08.244 --> 06:09.871
and neither is Peter.

06:10.038 --> 06:11.581
Oh, they're still
probably passed out cold.

06:11.748 --> 06:14.125
Or Andreas is so hung-over
that he can't move his lips

06:14.292 --> 06:15.835
to lie about
how he didn't do blow

06:16.002 --> 06:17.837
off a stripper's ass
last night.

06:18.004 --> 06:20.923
No, Andreas doesn't do blow.
He has terrible sinuses.

06:21.090 --> 06:24.135
No, this is the guy who calls me
12 times a day about nothing.

06:24.302 --> 06:26.095
They stop talking to you
when they get married.

06:26.262 --> 06:29.557
Which is fine. When they stop
listening, the trouble starts.

06:30.933 --> 06:33.019
He promised he would be
back in time to drive me

06:33.186 --> 06:34.604
to the bridal boutique -
it was his idea.

06:34.771 --> 06:36.064
SOPHIA: You can
worry about Andreas

06:36.230 --> 06:38.191
while you're
trying on dresses.

06:38.357 --> 06:39.859
(SIGHS)

06:40.026 --> 06:41.486
The designer
gets a $100 deposit,

06:41.652 --> 06:43.112
and I don't want to
lose my money.

06:43.279 --> 06:45.948
OK? Now, let's go.

06:47.742 --> 06:51.079
(HUMMING)

06:58.920 --> 07:01.547
(MAN YELLS)

07:04.884 --> 07:06.219
Give it back to me.

07:06.385 --> 07:08.513
It's mine! Come on!

07:08.679 --> 07:10.848
Now, beat it, Pancho.

07:11.015 --> 07:13.643
Go back to that pupuseria
you call a country.

07:13.810 --> 07:16.187
Give me that back,
and my name is not Pancho.

07:16.354 --> 07:18.231
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Now... Now, now, now, now.

07:18.397 --> 07:21.359
It seems like somebody here
has gone to the anger place,

07:21.526 --> 07:23.569
which is not a positive place.

07:23.736 --> 07:26.531
He took my personal shit,
including two cans of potatoes.

07:26.697 --> 07:30.409
The bag was left unattended,
therefore mine,

07:30.576 --> 07:32.870
according to
the laws of the streets.

07:33.037 --> 07:34.914
Streets? You're tripping.

07:35.081 --> 07:38.292
Give the young fella back
his bag and his potatoes.

07:38.459 --> 07:41.546
You can help yourself to as much
as you want from the truck.

07:41.712 --> 07:44.382
He's the one
always stirring up this shit.

07:44.549 --> 07:47.009
- And who asked you anyway?
- Alright. See...

07:47.176 --> 07:49.137
Now you're going
to the blame place,

07:49.303 --> 07:53.266
which is not a positive place...
or a creative place.

07:54.809 --> 07:56.894
(GROANS)

07:57.061 --> 07:58.688
(AITOR SIGHS)

07:58.855 --> 08:02.733
How about you go to
the shut-the-fuck-up place?

08:06.863 --> 08:09.282
- (GROANS)
- I warned you.

08:09.448 --> 08:12.326
But you wouldn't listen.

08:12.493 --> 08:15.079
(GROANS)

08:17.707 --> 08:18.833
(CAMERA CLICKS)

08:22.044 --> 08:23.421
(CAMERA CLICKS)

08:23.588 --> 08:25.006
AITOR:
You were fierce out there,

08:25.173 --> 08:27.758
getting all up
in McDougal's grill.

08:29.427 --> 08:30.720
He hit you.

08:30.887 --> 08:32.929
Well, he could have
done the same to you.

08:33.097 --> 08:34.515
Well, I've got size on him.

08:34.682 --> 08:36.308
And a face
that can take a punch

08:36.475 --> 08:37.768
and no-one would notice.

08:37.934 --> 08:39.854
That's it.

08:40.020 --> 08:43.232
That's why you seem
so familiar to me.

08:43.399 --> 08:45.318
I seem familiar?

08:47.361 --> 08:49.906
No-one has ever said that to me.

08:50.072 --> 08:52.491
You are a James Cameron heroine.

08:52.658 --> 08:54.410
(LAUGHS) Good Lord.

08:54.577 --> 08:59.040
No, a fierce and powerful woman,
a warrior, yet...

08:59.207 --> 09:01.584
..decidedly feminine,

09:01.751 --> 09:05.087
larger than life, literally,
and, uh,

09:05.254 --> 09:08.090
idiosyncratically beautiful.

09:08.257 --> 09:10.092
Boy, you must have been hit
pretty hard.

09:10.259 --> 09:12.929
- Do you know what day it is?
- It's Tuesday.

09:13.095 --> 09:17.225
I was, um...picking up
a load of corn niblets in town.

09:17.391 --> 09:19.477
Who's the President
of the United States?

09:19.644 --> 09:21.354
Like it even matters.

09:23.064 --> 09:26.108
The theatre's showing
one of James Cameron's movies,

09:26.275 --> 09:28.110
an under-appreciated classic

09:28.277 --> 09:30.279
portending
the greatness to come -

09:30.446 --> 09:31.822
'Piranha II'.

09:31.989 --> 09:33.491
Want to go?

09:34.617 --> 09:36.160
To the movies?

09:36.327 --> 09:38.079
And then after,

09:38.246 --> 09:40.706
we can go to the dump and, uh...

09:40.873 --> 09:44.210
..watch raccoons
forage for scraps and whatnot.

09:44.377 --> 09:46.337
It's a date night.

09:46.504 --> 09:48.547
A date.

09:48.714 --> 09:50.258
I can't.

09:50.424 --> 09:53.928
I'm not... I can't.

09:57.098 --> 09:59.558
(PHONE BEEPS)

10:02.979 --> 10:05.481
Hello. I'm returning a call
from this number.

10:05.648 --> 10:07.692
If you could give me
a call back, I'd appreciate it.

10:07.858 --> 10:10.361
- Thanks.
- Sorry I'm late.

10:13.447 --> 10:15.992
"From the desk
of Roman Godfrey"?

10:16.158 --> 10:19.912
My little sociopath a business
tycoon? Who would have thunk?

10:20.079 --> 10:22.873
He's got me running down wrong
numbers now looking for the kid.

10:23.040 --> 10:25.042
What'd you find out
about Shelley?

10:25.209 --> 10:29.005
Your daughter has taken up
residence at the Godfrey Mill.

10:29.171 --> 10:30.965
Oh, good heavens.

10:31.132 --> 10:35.845
That place is a rat's nest
of dope fiends, winos and bums.

10:36.012 --> 10:37.471
Truck they used
to move her things

10:37.638 --> 10:38.973
out of your apartment is...

10:39.140 --> 10:40.474
Her things?
That's stolen property.

10:40.641 --> 10:42.685
- That belongs to me.
- In any case...

10:42.852 --> 10:45.271
The vehicle is registered
to an Aitor Quantic

10:45.438 --> 10:47.106
of Two Rivers, Wisconsin.

10:47.273 --> 10:49.567
38 years old,
Pennsylvania driver's licence,

10:49.734 --> 10:51.527
probably the guy she rolls with.

10:51.694 --> 10:53.946
My daughter doesn't 'roll'
with anyone,

10:54.113 --> 10:56.157
certainly not some
middle-aged pervert.

10:56.324 --> 10:58.492
- I want him arrested.
- For?

10:58.659 --> 11:01.412
Burglary, for one.
He broke into my house.

11:01.579 --> 11:03.998
If she resides at that address,
it's not a burg...

11:04.165 --> 11:06.959
This predator is manipulating
a young girl's broken mind.

11:07.126 --> 11:09.128
- Why are you siding with him?
- (GLASS SHATTERS)

11:12.965 --> 11:14.550
What's the matter?

11:14.717 --> 11:16.010
You never seen a mother

11:16.177 --> 11:17.511
heartsick over
a troubled teen?

11:17.678 --> 11:20.097
I'm not taking his side.

11:20.264 --> 11:22.016
But you can't use the police
to declare war

11:22.183 --> 11:24.018
on some guy Shelley apparently
wants to hang out with.

11:24.185 --> 11:25.519
(SWEEPS GLASS)

11:25.686 --> 11:27.396
What man wants to hang out

11:27.563 --> 11:29.774
with a girl
that looks like that?

11:29.940 --> 11:33.319
I...I'll forbid her from
having anything to do with him.

11:33.486 --> 11:36.113
As a former bad boy, quickest
way to get a girl to bend over

11:36.280 --> 11:38.574
is for her mom or dad
to disapprove of you.

11:38.741 --> 11:40.242
It's like giving her
Spanish fly.

11:48.334 --> 11:52.588
OCHOA: Chango.
He's a protector of children.

11:52.755 --> 11:56.967
- What are you talking about?
- I want you to wear this.

11:58.177 --> 12:00.596
In my culture,
Chango's a big deal.

12:00.763 --> 12:02.681
Getting my daughter back
is gonna take

12:02.848 --> 12:04.350
a little more
than lucky charms.

12:04.517 --> 12:07.561
Chango was also the spirit guide
of self-control.

12:07.728 --> 12:11.148
Losing one's shit
accomplishes nothing.

12:14.235 --> 12:16.028
My gift to you.

12:22.952 --> 12:24.495
'Chango'?

12:24.662 --> 12:26.288
Spanish slang for 'monkey',

12:26.455 --> 12:28.582
and my grandmother's nickname
for me.

12:28.749 --> 12:30.626
Suits you.

12:33.796 --> 12:35.673
Thank you.

12:37.258 --> 12:39.176
WOMAN:
Is this a destination wedding?

12:39.343 --> 12:42.221
- Vegas? Beach in Hawaii?
- No, a church.

12:42.388 --> 12:44.473
- We're staying local.
- Hm.

12:44.640 --> 12:47.017
Gets complicated enough without
throwing airports into the mix.

12:47.184 --> 12:49.645
You'll want something
a little more formal.

12:49.812 --> 12:51.689
Maybe a cathedral train?

12:51.856 --> 12:53.816
She'll look just like an angel
floating on a cloud.

12:53.983 --> 12:55.359
Fuck!

12:55.526 --> 12:57.403
Or maybe a naughty princess.

12:57.570 --> 12:59.238
Let's talk about colour.

12:59.405 --> 13:01.490
This one comes in
natural, beige,

13:01.657 --> 13:03.617
bone and biscuit.

13:03.784 --> 13:05.953
- Could you try Bajram again?
- It just goes to voicemail.

13:08.122 --> 13:09.790
With your height,

13:09.957 --> 13:12.168
you could really own
the mermaid silhouette.

13:12.334 --> 13:14.837
Um... What colours
does it come in?

13:15.004 --> 13:16.297
Natural, beige,
bone and biscuit.

13:16.464 --> 13:18.257
Maybe they got arrested.

13:18.424 --> 13:20.718
Buy that dress quick before
all the money's used for bail.

13:20.885 --> 13:24.054
WOMAN: We can make this
out of organza, silk,

13:24.221 --> 13:27.224
batiste, shantung,
brocade or satin.

13:27.391 --> 13:29.727
<i>- (BEEP)</i>
- OK, Andreas.

13:29.894 --> 13:32.563
I'm officially pissed.
Where the fuck are you?

13:32.730 --> 13:34.982
All I can say is you better
have a good fucking excuse.

13:35.149 --> 13:36.233
(PHONE BEEPS)

13:44.074 --> 13:47.495
- What colours does it come in?
- Uh, natural, beige, bone and...

13:47.661 --> 13:48.996
Biscuit.

13:50.372 --> 13:52.541
(SIGHS) Biscuit.

13:54.710 --> 13:57.796
Have some more kimchi.
There's plenty.

13:57.963 --> 13:59.673
AITOR: We got
a lot of this stuff.

14:01.800 --> 14:03.761
You ready to get back
on that stage?

14:03.928 --> 14:05.888
This is when I could
probably use those drugs

14:06.055 --> 14:07.723
they were giving me.

14:07.890 --> 14:10.100
I don't want to go up there
and keel over again.

14:12.186 --> 14:15.356
Alright. Here's what you do
when you get nervous.

14:17.066 --> 14:19.902
You look at nervous,
and you say,

14:20.069 --> 14:21.904
"Welcome.

14:22.071 --> 14:25.574
"I recognise you.
You're nervous.

14:25.741 --> 14:27.952
"Who do you belong to?"

14:29.370 --> 14:31.080
And you look around,
you say, "Hey!

14:31.247 --> 14:34.291
"Anybody lose nervous?
He's right over here."

14:34.458 --> 14:37.002
You go do what you got to do,
and you let somebody else

14:37.169 --> 14:39.088
figure out
who nervous belongs to.

14:39.255 --> 14:41.090
Got it.

14:41.257 --> 14:44.134
And, uh, push the kimchi.
We got a shitload.

14:47.888 --> 14:49.265
WOMAN: Yeah, girl!

14:49.431 --> 14:52.184
(PEOPLE CHEER)

15:04.280 --> 15:07.032
I wrote something
I was gonna read to you today.

15:07.199 --> 15:10.202
Then I came across
something I like better

15:10.369 --> 15:12.538
because it reminds me...

15:16.875 --> 15:19.753
It reminds me
of someone I love very much

15:19.920 --> 15:22.131
who I miss a lot.

15:26.093 --> 15:28.804
The poem was written
by Richard Brautigan.

15:28.971 --> 15:32.933
It's called 'Boo, Forever'.

15:34.351 --> 15:37.730
This is for you, Uncle Norman,
wherever you are.

15:43.319 --> 15:47.156
"Spinning like a ghost
on the bottom of a top,

15:47.323 --> 15:52.494
"I am haunted by all the space
I will live without you."

15:56.832 --> 15:59.001
(APPLAUSE AND CHEERING)

16:06.967 --> 16:09.428
Uh, there's more kimchi
than we know what to do with.

16:09.595 --> 16:12.431
Take as much as you like.
Give some to your friends.

16:15.184 --> 16:17.603
Pass along the abundance.

16:35.412 --> 16:37.373
So this is how
you've been spending your time

16:37.539 --> 16:40.834
while I've been practically
catatonic with worry?

16:41.001 --> 16:43.045
Mother, what are you doing here?

16:43.212 --> 16:46.382
Well, I hope you're pleased,
sullying the Godfrey name

16:46.548 --> 16:50.928
while slumming with these
filthy, lice-infested halfwits.

16:51.095 --> 16:54.932
After all we've done, trying
to rescue you from insanity,

16:55.099 --> 16:56.934
this is how you repay us?

16:58.352 --> 17:00.479
(LAUGHS)

17:00.646 --> 17:03.607
(BOTH LAUGH)

17:06.902 --> 17:09.154
Welcome to Rooster Poot.

17:09.320 --> 17:11.949
- I am Aitor Quantic.
- Oh, I know who you are.

17:12.116 --> 17:14.910
And you're going to wish
we never crossed paths.

17:16.369 --> 17:18.579
Come along, dear -
let's get you home and deloused

17:18.747 --> 17:20.665
before you go completely insane.

17:20.833 --> 17:25.546
I've never felt more sane
in my life.

17:32.094 --> 17:35.264
Are you coming home? Do I need
to send for men in white coats?

17:36.265 --> 17:40.853
I'm starting to think maybe
I'm not the one who's crazy.

17:49.611 --> 17:51.572
So that was Mom.

17:51.739 --> 17:53.991
Yep.

17:55.743 --> 17:58.245
What time is that movie?

17:58.412 --> 18:00.372
OLIVIA: You know
who's responsible for this?

18:00.539 --> 18:03.542
Labour unions, with their
brotherhoods and picket signs,

18:03.709 --> 18:06.336
shutting down the factories
that built this country,

18:06.503 --> 18:09.965
turning the Godfrey Mill into
the Black Hole of Hemlock Grove,

18:10.132 --> 18:12.760
a cesspool
of filth and indolence.

18:12.926 --> 18:14.803
Garbage-eaters and idiots

18:14.970 --> 18:16.680
defecating
in front of each other.

18:16.847 --> 18:19.349
And this is where my daughter
feels right at home.

18:19.516 --> 18:22.019
This is not my fault.
This is so not my fault.

18:22.186 --> 18:23.979
(SIGHS)

18:24.146 --> 18:27.316
How could I have failed
so miserably?

18:27.483 --> 18:29.902
First Roman, now Shelley.

18:30.068 --> 18:33.447
I have half a mind to run
screaming for the hills myself.
I'm not even your kid.

18:33.614 --> 18:36.116
All those hours in labour
pushing and screaming, for what?

18:36.283 --> 18:38.786
To be told I don't matter,
I don't count for anything?

18:38.952 --> 18:40.746
Now you know
how Annie feels.

18:43.123 --> 18:45.250
That is her name, isn't it?

18:45.417 --> 18:47.753
Your daughter who came
looking for you the other day

18:47.920 --> 18:49.379
who you sent packing?

18:49.546 --> 18:51.340
For someone who spent
all those years onstage,

18:51.507 --> 18:53.217
that was
a mighty thin performance.

18:56.136 --> 18:58.806
She'd probably end up
hating me anyway.

18:58.972 --> 19:02.392
Or you get a fresh start and
make sure that doesn't happen.

19:04.186 --> 19:06.146
I might actually like my father

19:06.313 --> 19:08.023
if I was meeting him
for the first time.

19:08.190 --> 19:09.483
And who knows?

19:09.650 --> 19:10.984
Maybe you get
a few pointers

19:11.151 --> 19:13.070
