22:35.522 --> 22:37.315
(GRUNTS)

22:37.482 --> 22:40.485
(GENTLE MUSIC)

23:11.058 --> 23:13.477
ANNIE: He was a surgeon
at the base in Basra.

23:13.643 --> 23:17.898
I was a Red Cross nurse
at a refugee hospital.

23:18.065 --> 23:20.317
- He was handsome.
- Mmm.

23:20.484 --> 23:22.277
Love at first sight

23:22.444 --> 23:26.990
over amputations
and sucking chest wounds.

23:27.157 --> 23:31.286
And here is your granddaughter,
Katarina.

23:31.453 --> 23:35.457
She's seven there.
High scorer for her team.

23:36.833 --> 23:40.754
That was taken
a week before the accident.

23:42.380 --> 23:43.840
She has your eyes.

23:50.097 --> 23:53.975
Pryce tried to play it off, but
he's not that good of an actor.

23:54.142 --> 23:57.229
The coincidence of him
mentioning evidence of Spivak

23:57.395 --> 24:00.190
the day after Ochoa
showed us that picture

24:00.357 --> 24:02.359
strikes me
as awfully coincidental.

24:02.526 --> 24:04.569
- (PHONE BUZZES)
- You gonna answer that?

24:10.492 --> 24:13.161
Logic would suggest
Ochoa's the leak.

24:13.328 --> 24:14.955
I mean,
we already don't trust him.

24:15.122 --> 24:16.998
- Right.
- Somehow...

24:17.165 --> 24:21.753
Olivia, toxic, manipulative cunt
that she is,

24:21.920 --> 24:23.880
got a hook into him.

24:24.047 --> 24:26.133
So I left him a message
with his landlord

24:26.299 --> 24:28.009
saying it was from Olivia,

24:28.176 --> 24:30.387
to meet her,
the same place as last time.

24:30.554 --> 24:32.556
20 bucks says
he'll take the bait.

24:32.722 --> 24:34.599
Yeah.

24:38.061 --> 24:39.771
Peter?

24:41.189 --> 24:42.649
Peter?

24:46.319 --> 24:47.779
Are you OK?

24:50.240 --> 24:51.700
PETER: Here he is.

24:53.076 --> 24:55.078
(STARTS CAR)

25:10.552 --> 25:13.763
They taught me everything I'll
ever need to know about faith.

25:13.930 --> 25:15.932
Katarina especially.

25:16.099 --> 25:18.852
She died in my arms.

25:21.479 --> 25:23.398
But I know she'll...

25:23.565 --> 25:25.650
..always be...

25:25.817 --> 25:30.697
..perfect, whole and complete,
wherever she is.

25:32.365 --> 25:34.451
To me, 'faith' is a word
that describes something

25:34.618 --> 25:37.162
you know isn't real
but you wish it was.

25:37.329 --> 25:40.790
'Faith' is a...
a sad word, in a way.

25:43.501 --> 25:45.128
What do you believe in?

25:47.255 --> 25:49.132
I believe in the world

25:49.299 --> 25:51.343
and all its hot mess.

25:53.178 --> 25:55.513
The gift of being upir
is you get to live in it

25:55.680 --> 25:57.599
for a very long time.

25:59.601 --> 26:02.604
(GENTLE PIANO MUSIC)

26:33.218 --> 26:35.262
(FALTERS AND STOPS)

26:35.428 --> 26:38.431
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

27:01.746 --> 27:04.624
(SIGHS AND SNIFFS)

27:06.084 --> 27:08.503
No light. Turn it off, please.

27:08.670 --> 27:10.588
No light.

27:15.343 --> 27:16.845
Thank you.

27:17.012 --> 27:18.888
It's just...

27:20.098 --> 27:21.766
..a thing of mine.

27:23.685 --> 27:27.522
I've been a nurse since 1914.

27:27.689 --> 27:32.444
I worked in a field hospital
during the Battle of the Marne.

27:33.737 --> 27:39.367
In seven days, there were
250,000 French casualties.

27:39.534 --> 27:42.037
You can't imagine.

27:42.203 --> 27:47.292
I-I...think I remember reading
something about that somewhere.

27:47.459 --> 27:50.879
Then I moved back to France
in 1944.

27:51.046 --> 27:55.550
My fiancÃ© at the time
was a Canadian army officer.

27:55.717 --> 27:58.678
- I was a nursing sister.
- What happened to him?

27:58.845 --> 28:03.433
He saw combat in the Ardennes
during the Battle of the Bulge.

28:03.600 --> 28:05.852
PTSD.

28:06.019 --> 28:08.396
We drifted apart.

28:09.731 --> 28:11.691
You do like soldier boys.

28:13.360 --> 28:15.278
And the war machine.

28:15.445 --> 28:17.906
Staying that close
to the meat grinder,

28:18.073 --> 28:20.700
you must have had an endless
supply of blood and guts,

28:20.867 --> 28:22.619
one great big buffet.

28:22.786 --> 28:25.997
That's not
why I became a combat nurse.

28:26.164 --> 28:30.168
- It was a way for me to atone.
- For what?

28:32.962 --> 28:35.006
All the innocent lives I took

28:35.173 --> 28:38.218
feeding in the world
when I was a young upir.

28:38.385 --> 28:40.720
I had an epiphany,
and...and ever since...

28:40.887 --> 28:42.847
Oh, please tell me
you're not one of those...

28:43.014 --> 28:45.225
..self-loathing vegan vampires.

28:45.392 --> 28:48.645
Not at all, but I think there is
a more humane way to feed.

28:48.812 --> 28:51.731
The fat man in a restaurant
does not feel the need

28:51.898 --> 28:53.775
to atone for his pork chop.

28:55.151 --> 28:57.904
(FUNKY MUSIC)

28:59.781 --> 29:03.201
(PIANO MUSIC)

29:07.789 --> 29:09.249
(MISSES NOTE)

29:20.260 --> 29:22.804
(PLAYS RANDOM NOTES)

29:25.223 --> 29:28.560
(SINISTER MUSIC)

29:29.769 --> 29:31.938
(FATHER GRUNTS)

29:42.532 --> 29:46.035
PRYCE: And that's the last time
I ever saw my father.

29:47.495 --> 29:50.915
You see, darkness for me...

29:51.958 --> 29:54.669
..washes away
all the bad things.

29:54.836 --> 29:57.464
They messed with your head
real good, buddy,

30:00.633 --> 30:03.136
'Cause that is some
fucked-up shit.

30:08.850 --> 30:12.687
OLIVIA: He was a...
a beautiful boy, strong.

30:12.854 --> 30:17.192
He had sweet eyes,
blue as robins' eggs,

30:17.358 --> 30:20.111
smelled like hay,
and he was always laughing.

30:20.278 --> 30:24.115
We were children -
babies, really.

30:25.200 --> 30:27.577
Grown-ups would never let us
be together, of course,

30:27.744 --> 30:29.579
a stable boy.

30:29.746 --> 30:32.248
We were gonna run away,
your father and I.

30:32.415 --> 30:35.418
- Where to?
- The Greek islands.

30:35.585 --> 30:37.754
I mean, we didn't even know
where Bucharest was,

30:37.921 --> 30:41.799
let alone Greece, but...
that was our grand scheme.

30:41.966 --> 30:44.844
We'd wait for the warm weather,
and then...

30:45.011 --> 30:48.723
..we'd steal away
in the middle of the night.

30:50.308 --> 30:52.018
- Very romantic.
- Mmm.

30:53.269 --> 30:55.313
He was gonna be a fisherman.

30:55.480 --> 30:56.856
And you?

30:57.023 --> 31:00.360
A fisherman's wife, I guess.

31:03.446 --> 31:05.740
When I found out
I was pregnant with you,

31:05.907 --> 31:08.618
I...I told him
we needed to leave sooner -

31:08.785 --> 31:11.079
you know,
before I started showing.

31:12.539 --> 31:15.333
So he told me he was going
to the next village

31:15.500 --> 31:17.335
to steal a plough horse.

31:18.419 --> 31:22.048
That was...
the last I saw of him.

31:24.008 --> 31:26.219
You must have been heartbroken.

31:27.387 --> 31:29.639
I cried and cried.

31:30.765 --> 31:32.225
I loved him.

31:33.393 --> 31:34.894
I missed him.

31:35.061 --> 31:36.604
Hated him.

31:36.771 --> 31:38.690
Loved him again.

31:40.441 --> 31:42.944
And by the time I delivered,
I was just...

31:43.111 --> 31:44.904
..angry.

31:46.322 --> 31:47.782
I mean, I'm grateful to him,
though.

31:47.949 --> 31:49.951
He taught me a valuable lesson.

31:50.118 --> 31:52.245
Men leave.

31:52.412 --> 31:54.789
- Not all men.
- All men.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.749
It's what they do.

31:56.916 --> 31:58.459
I mean, even your Tod.

31:58.626 --> 32:01.629
Maybe not at the time or
in the manner of his choosing,

32:01.796 --> 32:04.090
but...here you are alone.

32:06.384 --> 32:08.511
I know you have
your faith or whatever

32:08.678 --> 32:10.430
and you think
he's somewhere...

32:10.597 --> 32:13.182
..perfect, whole and...

32:13.349 --> 32:15.018
Complete. Yeah.

32:15.184 --> 32:16.603
But he's not here.

32:16.769 --> 32:19.230
But he is, in here.

32:19.397 --> 32:21.566
Just because I can't see him...

32:21.733 --> 32:24.235
Or smell him or touch him
or fuck him.

32:27.030 --> 32:29.449
All you can do is be angry.

32:29.616 --> 32:32.035
Angry, you can do alone.

32:40.335 --> 32:42.587
Scrounged up some...bronzing

32:42.754 --> 32:45.590
and defining...
sculpting fixative powder

32:45.757 --> 32:47.342
and lipstick.

32:47.508 --> 32:51.220
Can I ask you something
that stays here?

32:51.387 --> 32:53.264
First date?

32:53.431 --> 32:56.392
Pretty obvious, I guess.

32:56.559 --> 32:58.186
Don't trip.

32:58.353 --> 33:00.229
It's like going somewhere
by yourself,

33:00.396 --> 33:02.357
only with another person
hanging around.

33:06.861 --> 33:10.239
You know, I've graf-bombed faces
on plenty of buildings.

33:10.406 --> 33:12.950
If you want,
I can see what I can do.

33:13.117 --> 33:14.869
Thanks.

33:15.036 --> 33:16.829
You'd be at it for days.

33:16.996 --> 33:19.332
It would take
a lot of spackle, modelling clay

33:19.499 --> 33:22.126
and a hot glue gun
to renovate this facade.

33:22.293 --> 33:25.880
If Aitor wants to take me
to the movies or...whatever,

33:26.047 --> 33:28.883
it's gonna have to be as is.

33:29.050 --> 33:32.553
They pulled you out of me, and
then...and they took you away.

33:32.720 --> 33:36.099
They wouldn't let me hold you
or...or...or even look at you.

33:36.265 --> 33:40.436
I was...punished just for asking
where you'd been sent.

33:42.063 --> 33:44.232
I would lie awake at night
wondering...

33:44.399 --> 33:47.610
..where you were,
what...your life was like.

33:49.404 --> 33:51.698
Did you ever
come looking for me?

33:54.033 --> 33:56.369
Records being
the way they were in those days,

33:56.536 --> 33:58.413
there was no way
I could find you.

34:01.249 --> 34:04.127
But did you ever look for me?

34:06.337 --> 34:08.797
I...I always thought about you
on your birthday.

34:08.965 --> 34:11.134
And on Christmas Day.

34:11.300 --> 34:13.136
You had money.

34:13.302 --> 34:16.556
Did you hire someone
to track me down?

34:19.350 --> 34:21.601
It's not a hard question.

34:29.110 --> 34:30.902
No.

34:34.031 --> 34:37.118
And you sh...you should be
thankful for that.

34:39.954 --> 34:42.290
I'm not the world's best mom.

34:42.456 --> 34:44.917
I have two other children
who will tell you as much.

34:45.083 --> 34:47.670
We're not very close.

34:47.837 --> 34:51.215
And I...I take responsibility
for that.

34:53.384 --> 34:55.636
But I...I've learned
from my mistakes, and I...

34:55.803 --> 34:58.639
..I want things
to be different with us.

35:00.057 --> 35:01.434
We've been honest
with each other.

35:01.601 --> 35:03.519
We're different people

35:03.686 --> 35:05.605
who look at the world
differently.

35:06.898 --> 35:09.358
But I want us to look past
those differences,

35:09.525 --> 35:10.860
past the mistakes I made,

35:11.027 --> 35:13.988
past the circumstances
that separated us.

35:17.533 --> 35:20.745
And I want us to find the things
that draw us closer together.

35:25.249 --> 35:27.168
Will you do that with me?

35:29.003 --> 35:30.296
Yes.

35:30.463 --> 35:33.174
Oh, my firstborn.

35:33.341 --> 35:35.176
I've found you.

35:52.652 --> 35:54.153
(PHONE CHIMES)

36:05.706 --> 36:07.834
(ACCELERATES)

36:08.000 --> 36:09.210
(TYRES SCREECH)

36:09.377 --> 36:10.711
ROMAN: What's he doing?

36:10.878 --> 36:12.839
- Did he spot us?
- Hell if I know.

36:26.853 --> 36:28.521
ROMAN: Right here.
Turn here.

36:51.419 --> 36:53.337
Something you boys
curious about?

36:54.338 --> 36:57.717
Might want to ask
instead of skulking around

36:57.884 --> 37:00.052
like a couple of junior G men.

37:00.219 --> 37:02.096
Don't think I need to ask.

37:02.263 --> 37:04.432
I already know the answer.

37:04.599 --> 37:07.351
You were just on your way
to meet with Olivia just now,

37:07.518 --> 37:09.520
like you've been doing
all along.

37:09.687 --> 37:12.148
If your issue is do I have
other clients that I work for,

37:12.315 --> 37:14.483
you don't pay me enough
to buy my exclusivity.

37:14.650 --> 37:17.486
How is she paying you? Huh?

37:17.653 --> 37:19.113
I know for a fact
that she's broke

37:19.280 --> 37:20.781
since I'm the one
who cut her off.

37:20.948 --> 37:22.909
Taking it out in trade?

37:23.075 --> 37:25.119
Now you're asking questions
I can't answer.

37:25.286 --> 37:27.288
You might want to powwow
with the, uh,

37:27.455 --> 37:31.167
hippie fortune teller chick -
great tits, nice ass.

37:32.460 --> 37:33.753
Oh! (GROANS)

37:33.920 --> 37:35.296
(YELLS)

37:36.923 --> 37:39.550
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Easy, easy.

37:43.596 --> 37:45.681
(GROANS)

37:47.058 --> 37:49.769
ROMAN: What the fuck?
You trying to kill the guy?

37:52.313 --> 37:53.648
ROMAN: Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

37:53.814 --> 37:55.608
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

37:57.652 --> 38:01.155
- The fuck's wrong with you?
- (ENGINE REVS)

38:01.322 --> 38:03.407
(TYRES SQUEAL)

38:07.370 --> 38:09.372
What the fuck was that, Peter?

38:09.538 --> 38:11.374
Huh?

38:13.250 --> 38:14.877
What's going on with you?

38:16.587 --> 38:19.799
Andreas was executed
by the Croatian Mob last night.

38:21.884 --> 38:24.345
He made a porno
starring him and...

38:24.512 --> 38:26.555
..one of the shot-caller's
girls.

38:32.103 --> 38:35.064
Then I handed him over to
the Croatians to make the peace.

38:38.150 --> 38:40.861
Seven of our people got killed
on account of what he did.

38:41.028 --> 38:43.656
And he knew it. He knew it.

38:43.823 --> 38:46.117
But he was gonna go to war,
and he was gonna have

38:46.283 --> 38:47.618
more innocent people killed.

38:47.785 --> 38:49.120
I had to put him down

38:49.286 --> 38:51.122
before more innocent blood
was spilled, OK?

38:51.288 --> 38:54.250
I didn't have a choice.
I didn't have a choice. I swear.

39:01.007 --> 39:03.759
But does that piece of shit
go to his grave taking...

39:03.926 --> 39:06.095
..taking the mess
that he made with him?

39:06.262 --> 39:08.014
No, that'd be too easy.

39:11.017 --> 39:13.978
I mean, what am I supposed to do
with the dead body?

39:33.873 --> 39:35.875
PETER: Stop.

39:40.838 --> 39:42.423
He should be in there.

39:45.468 --> 39:49.055
(GASPS)

40:01.692 --> 40:03.360
I'll call Pryce,
give him a heads-up.

40:03.527 --> 40:06.030
About... About what?

40:07.239 --> 40:08.699
Getting rid of this.

40:10.284 --> 40:11.827
No.

40:11.994 --> 40:14.163
No, Andreas has to have
a funeral.

40:14.330 --> 40:16.040
Destiny needs closure.

40:16.207 --> 40:18.084
To mourn her dead.

40:18.250 --> 40:20.377
That's a bad idea, Peter.

40:20.544 --> 40:22.588
A corpse turns up
and police will be all over it.

40:22.755 --> 40:24.256
You don't want
that kind of exposure.

40:31.347 --> 40:32.807
No.

40:36.519 --> 40:37.686
Your call.

40:38.813 --> 40:40.147
ROMAN: Come on.
Let's get him.

40:40.314 --> 40:42.691
(PHONE RINGS)

40:42.858 --> 40:44.902
- (PHONE BEEPS)
- Hello?

40:45.069 --> 40:48.823
Detective Zach Israel, Erie PD.
Who am I speaking with?

40:50.116 --> 40:51.575
May I ask
what this is regarding?

40:51.742 --> 40:53.244
ISRAEL: Yeah, I'm...
I'm returning a call

40:53.410 --> 40:55.621
made from this number
to a Merrill Samis.

40:55.788 --> 40:57.414
I don't know who that is.

40:57.581 --> 40:59.917
ISRAEL: So you're not aware
that he's deceased?

41:00.084 --> 41:03.754
- No. I'm sorry to hear that.
- You called him three times.

41:03.921 --> 41:05.881
Oh, right. Um...

41:06.048 --> 41:07.633
Actually, I...
I was returning a call.

41:07.800 --> 41:09.426
He...he must have called me
by mistake.

41:09.593 --> 41:12.179
Three callbacks
to a number dialled by mistake -

41:12.346 --> 41:13.639
that's pretty tenacious.

41:13.806 --> 41:17.268
How about the words
'Helmet smorgasbord'?

41:17.434 --> 41:20.938
- Does that mean anything to you?
- Uh... Doesn't ring a bell.

41:21.105 --> 41:22.481
ISRAEL:
Well, you see, I'm asking

41:22.648 --> 41:25.192
because these deaths
are homicides.

41:26.902 --> 41:29.071
Listen.
I was just returning a call.

41:29.238 --> 41:31.073
What it was about,
I wouldn't want to speculate.

41:31.240 --> 41:33.993
Well... If you think of anything
that might shed some light...

41:34.160 --> 41:35.578
I'll be in touch.

41:35.744 --> 41:37.538
(PHONE BEEPS)

41:48.048 --> 41:51.051
Manager said they were shipped
the wrong print by mistake,

41:51.218 --> 41:53.470
so they're showing this
instead of 'Piranha II'.

41:53.637 --> 41:55.890
So we'll watch this.

41:56.056 --> 41:57.516
AITOR:
Well, it's unfortunate.

41:57.683 --> 41:59.393
I think you'd really enjoy
'Piranha II'.

41:59.560 --> 42:01.270
It foreshadows
many of the themes

42:01.437 --> 42:04.064
James Cameron explores
in his later work.

42:04.231 --> 42:05.733
Oh.

42:05.900 --> 42:07.526
The trope
of the female protagonist

42:07.693 --> 42:10.446
as a canary in a coalmine
warning of the impending doom

42:10.613 --> 42:13.032
makes its debut in 'Piranha II'.

42:14.116 --> 42:15.993
If you want,
we can ask for our money back

42:16.160 --> 42:18.245
and go see 'Piranha II'
another time.

42:18.412 --> 42:20.873
No, no.
The movie doesn't matter.

42:21.040 --> 42:24.251
I'm mostly interested
in spending time with you

42:24.418 --> 42:26.545
and get to know each other
better.

42:28.714 --> 42:31.425
- I'd like that too.
- MAN IN MOVIE: <i>Oh, come on.</i>

42:31.592 --> 42:34.011
<i>What if he's telling the truth?</i>

42:35.554 --> 42:37.014
WOMAN: <i>It's possible.</i>

42:38.599 --> 42:41.101
You ever heard of
the Anthropocene extinction?

42:41.268 --> 42:43.062
No.

42:43.229 --> 42:46.106
It's the end of life
on this planet as we know it

42:46.273 --> 42:48.984
on account of man - that's what
'Anthropocene' means.

42:49.151 --> 42:51.362
It's happening as we speak.

42:51.528 --> 42:52.988
Oh.

42:53.155 --> 42:56.075
'Piranha II'
is an early manifesto

42:56.242 --> 42:59.036
bearing witness
to the ecological destruction

42:59.203 --> 43:02.039
caused by man's interference
in the natural order,

43:02.206 --> 43:03.749
symbolised in the film

43:03.916 --> 43:05.834
by genetically engineered

43:06.001 --> 43:07.878
flying carnivorous grunions.

43:08.045 --> 43:09.838
Oh.

43:12.383 --> 43:14.176
It's also a romance.

43:49.753 --> 43:51.088
Think this is OK?

43:51.255 --> 43:52.673
Except for
the surveillance cameras

43:52.840 --> 43:54.466
we won't know about
until the cops come knocking?

43:54.633 --> 43:55.718
Sure.

44:03.017 --> 44:05.269
(CAR DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

44:09.440 --> 44:11.483
(SIGHS)

44:13.193 --> 44:14.570
On three.

44:14.737 --> 44:17.364
One...two...three.

44:17.531 --> 44:19.783
PETER: Oh, shit.

44:25.331 --> 44:27.291
I better call in a tip to 911,

44:27.458 --> 44:29.251
so he's not out here
too long.

44:31.795 --> 44:33.255
I'll do it.

44:33.422 --> 44:36.050
You need to stay as
far away from this as you can.

44:37.301 --> 44:38.761
Thank you.

44:45.309 --> 44:47.311
Come on. We got to go.

44:59.573 --> 45:01.658
Come on, Peter.
We got to get out of here.

45:04.787 --> 45:07.164
(CAR DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

45:07.331 --> 45:09.750
- (ENGINE STARTS)
- (CAR DOOR CLOSES)

45:25.766 --> 45:27.059
AITOR:
The warrior mother's journey

45:27.226 --> 45:29.269
takes her into the dark realm -

45:29.436 --> 45:31.605
in this case, the sunken ship -

45:31.772 --> 45:33.190
to confront death

45:33.357 --> 45:35.442
and returns
enlightened and empowered.

45:35.609 --> 45:37.027
Classic monomyth stuff.

45:37.194 --> 45:39.613
Aitor, you are
a really interesting guy

45:39.780 --> 45:42.449
with a lot of really interesting
things to say.

45:42.616 --> 45:44.952
But I should shut up
and let you watch this movie.

45:45.119 --> 45:47.371
It's pretty good, actually.

45:47.538 --> 45:50.207
I talk a blue streak
when I get nervous.

45:51.875 --> 45:54.795
You're nervous? I thought...

45:54.962 --> 45:57.631
You mean, "Hey, everybody,
I got nervous over here.

45:57.798 --> 45:59.883
"Who does nervous belong to?"

46:00.050 --> 46:04.346
I invariably find out
nervous belongs to me.

46:04.513 --> 46:06.807
What are you nervous about?

46:08.475 --> 46:10.561
A lot of things.

46:10.727 --> 46:12.813
Mostly getting close to people.

46:14.857 --> 46:16.650
I understand.

46:18.068 --> 46:19.945
Do I make you nervous?

46:20.112 --> 46:21.572
No.

46:21.738 --> 46:23.699
But there is
the whole issue of...

46:23.866 --> 46:27.870
..comportment regarding a...
first kiss situation

46:28.036 --> 46:32.458
presenting itself, should we...
continue down this path,

46:32.624 --> 46:34.418
which...

46:34.585 --> 46:36.003
..objectively speaking,

46:36.170 --> 46:38.630
is completely terrifying.

46:38.797 --> 46:41.550
First...kiss?

46:41.717 --> 46:44.845
See? I already ruined it.

46:46.597 --> 46:48.223
Forget I said anything.

46:48.390 --> 46:51.268
You want to kiss me?

46:52.895 --> 46:54.855
Not if you don't want me to.

46:56.231 --> 46:58.066
See, this is where I struggle,

46:58.233 --> 47:01.111
in that grey zone
of getting close to someone,

47:01.278 --> 47:03.989
knowing or not knowing
when it's appropriate

47:04.156 --> 47:06.200
or not appropriate,
as the case may...

47:06.366 --> 47:09.328
I'd be fine with it...I think.

47:09.495 --> 47:10.787
Though maybe
it would be better

47:10.954 --> 47:13.373
if we just called it
our second kiss.

47:15.375 --> 47:18.378
<i>(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY
IN MOVIE)</i>

47:20.088 --> 47:22.299
WOMAN: <i>That's your job?
You're a field inspector.</i>

47:22.466 --> 47:25.177
MAN: <i>Well, maybe I should
find me some other kind of work.</i>

47:26.345 --> 47:28.514
<i>Because it ain't like
the old days.</i>

47:28.680 --> 47:32.434
<i>It's bad, dangerous and ugly
down there, Kelly.</i>

47:32.601 --> 47:35.229
<i>Would you believe the other day,
I saw a rat this big?</i>

47:35.395 --> 47:37.481
<i>- Are you through?
- No, I mean it!</i>

47:37.648 --> 47:39.650
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

47:41.777 --> 47:44.530
I was worried when I didn't
hear back, but, um...

47:46.240 --> 47:48.158
- Are you OK?
- I'm good.

47:48.325 --> 47:50.452
You've hurt yourself.

47:50.619 --> 47:52.788
- Here, let me see.
- Really. I'm fine.

47:52.955 --> 47:56.833
You know what? You need
a stiff drink and a good meal.

47:57.000 --> 47:58.627
There's this little bistro
in Sewickley

47:58.794 --> 48:00.087
I've been meaning to try.

48:00.254 --> 48:01.338
I really can't.

48:03.549 --> 48:06.009
Well, I suppose we could
stay here and order pizza

48:06.176 --> 48:07.678
like a couple of teenagers.

48:07.844 --> 48:09.513
Roman fired me.

48:09.680 --> 48:12.766
That pissy little prick.

48:12.933 --> 48:16.562
No, trust me. Not working
for your son is a good thing.

48:16.728 --> 48:18.397
I've been doing some digging,
and...

48:18.564 --> 48:21.316
..the stuff I'm coming up with
is about as bad as it gets.

48:21.483 --> 48:23.360
Forget about Roman.

48:24.361 --> 48:26.863
I want to tell you all about
my afternoon with Annie.

48:27.030 --> 48:30.534
I...I keep a fishing boat
down in the Florida Keys.

48:30.701 --> 48:33.787
I think I should go spend
some quality time on board,

48:33.954 --> 48:36.206
far, far away from here.

48:36.373 --> 48:38.166
What are you saying?

48:38.333 --> 48:40.794
If I leave now,
ahead of rush hour,

48:40.961 --> 48:43.505
I can...get there
by sunset tomorrow.

48:45.716 --> 48:47.009
What about Shelley?

48:47.175 --> 48:49.261
I got a buddy of mine
checking in on that.

48:50.721 --> 48:53.056
That guy she's with, turns out,
has some priors.

48:53.223 --> 48:54.850
So that's all in FedEx.

48:55.017 --> 48:58.061
You need to help me
find my granddaughter.

48:58.228 --> 49:00.522
I hate to say it,
but you know as well as anyone,

49:00.689 --> 49:02.399
I'm turning up nothing
on that.

49:02.566 --> 49:04.985
And Roman - I mean,
you know what he's capable of.

49:05.152 --> 49:08.030
Imagine how I feel.
You can't go.

49:08.196 --> 49:10.866
My car is packed.
I'm checked out of my place.

49:16.204 --> 49:17.205
And us?

49:19.124 --> 49:21.835
Just really...
beginning to know one another.

49:24.880 --> 49:28.133
For whatever reason,
you and I really seem to click.

49:29.217 --> 49:32.721
You seem to understand me.
Most men...don't.

49:32.888 --> 49:35.057
I've enjoyed
working with you too.

49:35.223 --> 49:38.018
And we'll definitely
stay in touch.

49:38.185 --> 49:41.104
You should plan a trip.
Get you out on the boat.

49:41.271 --> 49:43.815
Gulf Stream's
just a couple miles offshore.

49:43.982 --> 49:46.735
There's a marlin out there with
your name on it. No question.

49:50.238 --> 49:52.240
You have to stay
in Hemlock Grove.

49:52.407 --> 49:55.535
I...I need you here with me.

49:57.037 --> 49:58.538
Come here.

50:07.881 --> 50:09.424
Don't leave.

50:09.591 --> 50:11.593
We'll see each other soon.

50:15.681 --> 50:18.850
What do I have to do
to make you stay?

50:19.976 --> 50:22.813
AITOR: Most people think
the world's gonna end

50:22.979 --> 50:24.398
in a ball of fire

50:24.564 --> 50:27.484
or a blinding flash and a...

50:27.651 --> 50:30.112
..giant mushroom cloud.

50:31.947 --> 50:35.158
Personally, I think Armageddon's
happening all around us,

50:35.325 --> 50:37.703
in slow motion.

50:40.080 --> 50:44.376
"This is the way the world ends,
not with a bang but a whimper"?

50:44.543 --> 50:46.461
Yep.

50:50.507 --> 50:52.426
Does it depress you?

50:54.010 --> 50:56.054
Well, February depresses me.

50:57.556 --> 50:59.641
Armageddon, I'm OK with.

50:59.808 --> 51:01.935
I mean...

51:02.102 --> 51:04.062
- What are you gonna do?
- (LAUGHS)

51:04.229 --> 51:07.107
- Hey, look. From the video.
- Hey, it's Frankenstein.

51:07.274 --> 51:09.568
- Sad.
- In the flesh.

51:09.735 --> 51:12.738
- A lot of flesh, bro.
- Shut the hell up and show her.

51:12.904 --> 51:15.615
<i>(MAN RAPS ON VIDEO)</i>

51:15.782 --> 51:17.826
MAN 2: Hey. That's you.

51:19.953 --> 51:21.246
WOMAN: Cool.

51:21.413 --> 51:23.373
- MAN: Sick.
- WOMAN: Yeah. Awesome.

51:23.540 --> 51:26.585
- On fire.
- You're on YouTube.

51:26.752 --> 51:28.503
4,000 hits so far.

51:28.670 --> 51:31.047
And Rich Girl just picked it up
on their blog.

51:31.214 --> 51:33.341
You're gonna be a star.

51:33.508 --> 51:35.969
WOMAN: So cool.

51:36.136 --> 51:38.972
(LAUGHS) Told you guys.
Come on. Let's go.

51:50.567 --> 51:52.360
WOMAN: 911.
What's your emergency?

51:52.527 --> 51:55.197
(DISGUISED VOICE) There's a man
on the sidewalk passed out.

51:55.363 --> 51:57.365
I don't think he's breathing.

51:57.532 --> 51:59.034
What's the address?

51:59.201 --> 52:01.244
The Nestor building
on Hope Road.

52:01.411 --> 52:04.122
- I don't know the number.
- Paramedics are on their way.

52:04.289 --> 52:08.251
- Is the man injured?
- All I know is he won't wake up.

